This paper deals with access control policy languages and the design of policy miners using machine learning and combinatorial algorithms. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the experimental evaluation of the policy miners, which involves data analysis and machine learning techniques such as search algorithms, which could be classified under machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the design of policy miners, which could be classified under software engineering (cs.SE).
